  <HEADLINE>
   <S PAR="1" RSNT="1" SNO="1">Heavy penalty for endangered species trading</S>
  </HEADLINE>
  <TEXT>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Traders are reminded that trading or possessing highly endangered species may face heavy penalty.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The appeal was made by the Agriculture and Fisheries Department (AFD) after a trader today (Tuesday) received a penalty for illegal possession of shahtoosh shawls made from the highly endangered Tibetan antelopes.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='2' SNO='4'>She was fined $300,000 and sentenced to three months' imprisonment suspended for 12 months.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The 130 shawls involved were also mandatorily forfeited to the Government.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>An AFD spokesman said: "We invited an American expert to give professional evidence during the hearing of the case and AFD will spare no effort in combating illegal activities related to endangered species."</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The defendant was convicted in South Kowloon Magistracy in February.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The spokesman said it was an offence to import, export or possess endangered species without a licence under the Animals and Plants (Protection of Endangered Species) Ordinance.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>"An offender is liable to a maximum fine of $5 million and two years' imprisonment upon conviction," he added.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>He also took the opportunity to urge members of the public to report any illegal activities on endangered species to AFD's Endangered Protection Section on 2733 2286 or 2733 2117.</S>
  </TEXT>
